dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, spot heights, and gradient tints.  Five classes of railways and five classes of roads are shown.  Covers area west from Marainviller, France to Baden-Baden, Germany to the west, and north from Saaralben (Alwe, France) to Neu-Breisach (Neuf-Brisach, France) to the south. Strassburg (Strasbourg) roughly at right center of sheet.  Sheet K.49, Strassburg from series originally issued in various editions by Great Britain, War Office, Geographical Section, General Staff, No. 4346.  For use by War and Navy Department Agencies only. Not for sale or distribution..  Military grid.  Nord de Guerre Zone Grid ... Spheroid, Du Plessis. ... Lambert Zone II Grid ... Spheroid, Clarke 1880..  Cataloging agency's copy overprinted with 4 coordinate scale circles with center points located roughly at E 6°/N 48°45ʹ; E 7°37ʹ/N 48°45ʹ; E 8°/N 48°15ʹ; E 7°18ʹ/N 48°15ʹ.  IXA.  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Includes legend, Incidence of grid letters diagrams, Convergence for corners of this sheet diagram, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Grid data: Nord de Guerre Grid and Lambert Zone II Grid, index to adjoining sheets, index to corresponding 1:100,000 scale sheets, conversion table, Authorities, and Glossary.  C.T. 5.44..
